Extensions for Non-ASCII Text
1996", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC2047.html", target="_top", tooltip="This particular document is the third document in the series.  It describes extensions to RFC 822 to allow non-US-ASCII text data in Internet mail header fields. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"];
  cites -> RFC2047;
  RFC2978 [label="RFC2978
IANA Charset Registration Procedures
2000", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC2978.html", target="_top", tooltip="Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) and various other Internet protocols are capable of using many different charsets.  This in turn means that the ability to label different charsets is essential.  This document specifies an Internet Best Current Practices for the Internet Community, and requests discussion and suggestions for improvements."];
